# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# LLM provider — pick one. Defaults to github if unset.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

LLM_PROVIDER=github        # one of: github | ollama | claude | openai
# LLM_MODEL=openai/gpt-4.1-mini  # optional override; each provider has a default

# Optional failover: set LLM_FALLBACK_PROVIDER to one of the above
# (different from LLM_PROVIDER). If the primary returns a 5xx / 429 /
# throws before streaming starts, streamChat auto-retries with this
# fallback. Useful pairing: github (free) + ollama (paid reliable).
# LLM_FALLBACK_PROVIDER=ollama

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# GitHub Models — set if LLM_PROVIDER=github (or as a fallback target).
# Free-tier OpenAI-compatible inference via GitHub's own endpoint.
# Any GitHub account works; no Copilot subscription required.
#
# Create a fine-grained PAT at:
#   github.com/settings/personal-access-tokens
# Scopes needed: "Models: read" (under Account permissions)
#
# Default model: openai/gpt-4.1-mini (namespaced format expected by
# the GitHub Models endpoint; prefix with "openai/", "meta/",
# "deepseek/" etc. — see github.com/marketplace/models for the
# full catalog). Free tier has per-minute token budgets, so keep
# maxTokens modest in lib/llm/config.ts.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# GITHUB_TOKEN=github_pat_...

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Ollama — set if LLM_PROVIDER=ollama
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# LOCAL daemon: leave both blank (or set OLLAMA_BASE_URL to http://localhost:11434)
# OLLAMA CLOUD: set OLLAMA_API_KEY; base URL auto-resolves to https://ollama.com
# OLLAMA_BASE_URL=https://ollama.com
# OLLAMA_API_KEY=your-ollama-key

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Claude — set if LLM_PROVIDER=claude
# Get key at https://console.anthropic.com/
# Default model: claude-haiku-4-5-20251001
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# OpenAI — set if LLM_PROVIDER=openai
# Get key at https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
# Default model: gpt-4.1-mini
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Upstash Redis — required for rate limiting + logging in production.
# Install the Vercel-Upstash integration:
# https://vercel.com/integrations/upstash → auto-populates KV_* vars
# on deploy. Leave blank in local dev — ratelimit + logging fail-open.
#
# The code reads either naming scheme:
#   UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL  / UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN  (manual setup)
#   KV_REST_API_URL         / KV_REST_API_TOKEN         (Vercel integration)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL=https://<your-db>.upstash.io
# UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN=...

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Logging — static salt for hashing IPs before writing to Redis.
# Generate with `openssl rand -hex 16`. If unset, logging still
# works but IPs are hashed with a weak default (dev only).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# LOG_SALT=...
